 on the object at its lowest point. (b) If the spring has a force constant of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi/><m:mtext>N/m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"10" "." 0`"N/m"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and a 0.25-kg-mass object is set in motion as described, find the amplitude of the oscillations. (c) Find the maximum velocity. </para></problem></exercise>
